-- AC Milan Appoints Massimiliano Allegri as Soccer Coach to Replace Leonardo
-- Dan Baynes
-- 2010-06-25T11:46:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/ac-milan-appoints-massimiliano-allegri-as-soccer-coach-to-replace-leonardo.html

          
          
             Italian Serie A soccer club AC Milan
said it appointed Massimiliano Allegri as its new coach.  
 Allegri, who replaces Brazilian Leonardo, signed a contract
with the seven-time European champion through June 30, 2012, the
club said in a statement on its website.  
          
          


  


        